{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-chapter-level-2-chapter-level-2-tsx","path":"/topics/anaemia-iron-deficiency/how-this-topic-was-developed/evidence-exclusion-criteria/","result":{"pageContext":{"chapter":{"id":"ddead63b-587e-5359-85da-62aa7b78caab","slug":"evidence-exclusion-criteria","fullItemName":"Evidence exclusion criteria","depth":2,"htmlHeader":"<!-- begin field 3dddccce-650f-4c83-9f7f-a7f20187b594 --><h2>Evidence exclusion criteria</h2><!-- end field 3dddccce-650f-4c83-9f7f-a7f20187b594 -->","summary":null,"htmlStringContent":"<!-- begin item c43b35de-0838-449c-92c1-a7f20187a3cf --><!-- begin field d5996d0d-79ec-4c02-ab63-a7f20187b594 --><h2>Our policy</h2><!-- end field d5996d0d-79ec-4c02-ab63-a7f20187b594 --><!-- begin field 571e99a9-56fe-49f2-b2e5-a7f20187b594 --><p>Scoping a literature search, and reviewing the evidence for CKS is a methodical and systematic process that is carried out by the lead clinical author for each topic. Relevant evidence is gathered in order that the clinical author can make fully informed decisions and recommendations. It is important to note that some evidence may be excluded for a variety of reasons. These reasons may be applied across all CKS topics or may be specific to a given topic.</p><p>Studies identified during literature searches are reviewed to identify the most appropriate information to author a CKS topic, ensuring any recommendations are based on the best evidence. We use the principles of the GRADE and PICOT approaches to assess the quality of published research. We use the principles of AGREE II to assess the quality of published guidelines.</p><!-- end field 571e99a9-56fe-49f2-b2e5-a7f20187b594 --><!-- begin field 5115767c-242a-42e9-8469-a7f20187b594 --><h2>Standard exclusions for scoping literature:</h2><!-- end field 5115767c-242a-42e9-8469-a7f20187b594 --><!-- begin field 9fc7c896-3de3-4033-8f38-a7f20187b594 --><ul><li>Animal studies</li><li>Original research is not written in English</li></ul><!-- end field 9fc7c896-3de3-4033-8f38-a7f20187b594 --><!-- begin field 61f1a2e7-c571-46ad-be9b-a7f20187b594 --><h2>Possible exclusions for reviewed literature:</h2><!-- end field 61f1a2e7-c571-46ad-be9b-a7f20187b594 --><!-- begin field 8f00bc6c-2c1c-4c8a-a1d2-a7f20187b594 --><ul><li>Sample size too small or study underpowered</li><li>Bias evident or promotional literature</li><li>Population not relevant</li><li>Intervention/treatment not relevant</li><li>Outcomes not relevant</li><li>Outcomes have no clear evidence of clinical effectiveness</li><li>Setting not relevant</li><li>Not relevant to UK</li><li>Incorrect study type</li><li>Review article</li><li>Duplicate reference</li></ul><!-- end field 8f00bc6c-2c1c-4c8a-a1d2-a7f20187b594 --><!-- end item c43b35de-0838-449c-92c1-a7f20187a3cf -->","topic":{"id":"fb1f29c6-7885-5985-9c50-f60728d0c217","topicId":"fe022fea-3c66-4f2f-a8bf-ad115ab4c9af","topicName":"Anaemia - iron deficiency","slug":"anaemia-iron-deficiency","lastRevised":"Last revised in September 2018","chapters":[{"id":"082948a7-cd90-5024-85e8-863331322afc","fullItemName":"Summary","slug":"summary","subChapters":[]},{"id":"aaac4ffb-4e68-543c-b203-556c7036da4f","fullItemName":"Have I got the right topic?","slug":"have-i-got-the-right-topic","subChapters":[]},{"id":"531a9e5e-3bbc-5238-b871-f84ab5fdfa4b","fullItemName":"How up-to-date is this topic?","slug":"how-up-to-date-is-this-topic","subChapters":[{"id":"012c21c3-ccf8-59b2-beb7-24de6a2916e8","slug":"changes","fullItemName":"Changes"},{"id":"8a94f45a-308e-567f-8f00-12c0ab02b734","slug":"update","fullItemName":"Update"}]},{"id":"132d2f2d-7cde-5976-bfdc-7baed43877d7","fullItemName":"Goals and outcome measures","slug":"goals-outcome-measures","subChapters":[{"id":"c865a525-034d-544e-ae07-3ba91a4f1ee8","slug":"goals","fullItemName":"Goals"},{"id":"25441aae-7584-5500-83b5-16ba4f39baf5","slug":"outcome-measures","fullItemName":"Outcome measures"},{"id":"0b28673c-36d4-5297-b18a-e0510a5b803e","slug":"audit-crite